{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἔπαλξ-ις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> (ἐπαλέξω) <b>means of defence</b>: mostly in <i>plural</i>, <b>battlements,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.263, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.7, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 30, 158 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1158, etc.; τὰς ἐ. ἀπώσαντες 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.23; αἱ οἰκίαι.. ἐπάλξεις λαμβάνουσι [prev. author] 4.69, compare 115. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> in <i>singular</i>, mostly, <b>line of battlements, parapet,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.381, +others (never in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ παρ᾽ ἔπαλξιν the defenders of the wall, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.13, compare 7.28, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 72 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, of individual <b>crenellations,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.21. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> generally, <b>defence, protection,</b> πλούτου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 381 (Lyric poetry); σωτηρίας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1203, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> court for trial of homicide, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Etymologicum Magnum” 353.26, “Anecdota Graeca - Bekker” 243. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G7360","accentedUnicode":"ἔπαλξις","shortDef":"a parapet","mediumDef":"a parapet","stepGloss":"a parapet","stepTransliteration":"epalxis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}